\answer{(1)\(\frac{\pi}{2}\)
(2)\(\frac{1}{6},1 + \frac{\sqrt{2}}{3} + \frac{\sqrt{5}}{3}\)}
\explain{(1)\(\because \bigtriangleup ABC中有c\text{sin}B + \sqrt{3}c\text{cos}B = \sqrt{3}a + b\)，\par
由正弦定理得，
\(\text{sin}C\text{sin}B + \sqrt{3}\text{sin}C\text{cos}B = \sqrt{3}\text{sin}A + \text{sin}B\)，\par
又将\(A = \pi - (B + C)\)代入得，
\(\text{sin}C\text{sin}B + \sqrt{3}\text{sin}C\text{cos}B = \sqrt{3}\text{sin}(B + C) + \text{sin}B\)，\par
展开得，
\(\text{sin}C\text{sin}B + \sqrt{3}\text{sin}C\text{cos}B = \sqrt{3}\left( \sin B\cos C + \cos B\sin C \right) + \text{sin}B\)，\par
整理得，
\(\left( \text{sin}C - \sqrt{3}\text{cos}C \right)\text{sin}B = \text{sin}B\)，\par
由\(B \in \left( 0,\pi \right),\text{sin}B \neq 0\)，\par
所以\(\text{sin}C - \sqrt{3}\text{cos}C = 1\)，
得\(\frac{1}{2}\text{sin}C - \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}\text{cos}C = \frac{1}{2}\)，
即\(\text{sin}\left( C - \frac{\pi}{3} \right) = \frac{1}{2}\)，\par
由\(C \in \left( 0,\pi \right)知- \frac{\pi}{3} < C - \frac{\pi}{3} < \frac{2\pi}{3}\)，
所以\(C - \frac{\pi}{3} = \frac{\pi}{6}\)，\par
故\(C = \frac{\pi}{2}\)．\par
(2)\(\because AD = DB,CE = 2EA,c = 2\)，\par
\(\therefore AD = 1,AE = \frac{1}{3}b,S_{\bigtriangleup ADE} = \frac{1}{2}AD \cdot AE\text{sin}A = \frac{1}{6}b\text{sin}A\)，\par
